# 4. あの日の出会い

An: *Sigh* I'm wiped out!
Mizuki: I know, right? I'm aching all over. Why do they have to make the chairs at school so hard?
An: Do you think so? They've never really bothered me, I guess.
Mizuki: What?! It can't be good for the body to sit like that for hours on end.
Mizuki: Personally, I don't understand how everyone can bear to be in a classroom for that long like it's normal.
An: I guess you don't come to school that often, do you Mizuki? And even when you do, you skip a whole bunch of classes.
An: So I'm even more grateful that you came in to help us today. You made everything really clear, and I made some good progress!
Mizuki: Don't mention it! It was more fun than I expected♪
Mizuki: Oh, more importantly, look over there! It's that apple pie place I told you about!
An: Wow. I can already smell them from here.
Mizuki: It has great reviews online. But, whoa... The place is rammed inside.
Mizuki: Hm...
Mizuki: If it's that crowded, I'll go and buy them myself. You wait out here.
An: Oh, are you sure? Thanks, Mizuki!
An: I wonder when Mizuki will be back...
An: Oh yeah. I can use spare moments like this for study. I should have time to do some vocabulary.
An: I studied so hard today that my head kinda hurts... But the others are putting in so much effort for our sakes that we have to pull our weight.
An: Um, where's that vocab list...
Classmate A: Oh, hi An!
An: Oh... What are you two doing here?
Classmate B: We're headed home from club! It was pretty intense today since the second-years made us run a ton...
Classmate A: Oh yeah, we heard about you taking supplementary classes. Apparently you might get held back a year?
An: Wait, what?! How do you know that?
Classmate B: Through the grapevine. I knew your grades weren't the best, but...oof.
Classmate A: But, I heard that they do these classes every year to help people out. I bet it'll all be fine as long as you take it seriously.
An: *Grimace* I hope so.
An: I have some friends with good grades who are helping me study, so I guess it'll be alright...
Classmate A: Oh, really? I guess you won't be needing us then.
An: Huh?
Classmate A: Earlier, we were all talking about helping you study if you needed it.
Classmate B: We're not exactly straight A students ourselves, but how does the saying go? Strength in numbers?
Classmate B: A bunch of people said they'd pitch in, so we'd be unstoppable if we combined forces.
An: You guys...
Classmate A: Well, anyway. If there's anything we can do to help, let us know. We'll be there for you.
Classmate B: Yeah, just like friends should!
An: Got it! Thanks, you two!
Classmate A: See you later, An!
Classmate B: Bye!
An: Hehe.
An: (I'm kinda happy. Not just Mizuki and the others, but everyone is jumping to help me out...)
Mizuki: Sorry, An! I got out as quick as I could. That place was so crowded.
An: No problem at all! I was just talking to my friends.
Mizuki: Your friends?
An: Yeah. Two of my classmates were passing by and said hello. They already know about the supplementary classes.
An: It was kinda embarrassing... But they let me know they've got my back, which made me feel better.
Mizuki: Really...? That's great!
Mizuki: Come to think of it, you really have a lot of friends, An. I always see you talking with people in other classes and years.
An: Do you think so? I'd say I have an average amount of friends.
Mizuki: No way! It's not even just students, you chat with the teachers and the custodian too. There's nothing average about getting on with so many different people so easily.
Mizuki: I'm the outgoing type myself, but you're on a different level.
An: Hm... Maybe? I never thought about it much...
An: Oh, maybe it's because I've been singing on Vivid Street for years?
Mizuki: Huh?
An: I grew up in a neighborhood where everyone loves music. And I've been singing there since I was little.
An: Whenever I did, all sorts of people would come and say hi, and I just naturally get to know them, I guess?
An: And, even if we got into fights, we'd always be closer by the end.
Mizuki: Really? Wait, fights...?!
An: Singing on the street can lead to arguments sometimes.
An: Vivid Street attracts a lot of young, intense types, and over time you start to have a history with them.
Mizuki: Wow... It sounds like a pretty wild place...
An: Hahaha. To be clear, they're not bad people. Everyone's just really passionate about music. And even when we do butt heads, it usually gets resolved with singing battles.
An: And after battling the same person a few times, you start to understand the passion and pride behind their singing...
An: Even if they grated on you at first, you start to recognize that you share that commitment to singing.
Mizuki: Oh, really?
An: Really. So, I guess that's why I'm this way. I've learned to just be genuine and direct with everyone I meet. That way, sooner or later we'll get to know each other and accept all the different parts of each other.
An: And I think that's why I don't have any trouble socializing and getting to know people.
Mizuki: Wow.
Mizuki: That's pretty cool. I had no idea you thought about it that way, An.
An: It's not like I think about this stuff all the time. That's just what came to mind when I gave it some thought just now.
An: If anything, I don't think about much at all usually.
Mizuki: Hahaha, is that so?
Mizuki: (Still...)
Mizuki: (An's amazing... I can't imagine being so confident about getting close to people and accepting each other.)
Mizuki: (That must be why, that time...)
Mizuki: (Phew... Finally lunch break.)
Mizuki: (Urgh, I don't wanna go to class in the afternoon... Maybe I'll ditch school once I eat...)
???: Hey! Akiyama, right?
Mizuki: Huh?
An: Nice to meet you! I'm An Shiraishi. You can call me An.
Mizuki: Uh... N-Nice to meet you.
An: Oh, did I startle you? Sorry about that!
An: I just wanted to get to know you since we're classmates and all!
Mizuki: Hahaha. Well, you did spook me a little, but don't sweat it.
Mizuki: You can call me Mizuki! Nice to meet you, An.
Mizuki: (It was right after we started high school, and everyone was giving me a wide berth... But An just came and talked to me like normal.)
Mizuki: (And she could do that because...)
Mizuki: (She believes it's possible to find common ground with everyone... And that's why she's friendly and direct with everyone she meets.)
An: Mizuki? Is something wrong?
Mizuki: Oh... Nope, I'm all good!
Mizuki: Wanna get going? It's getting a little chilly out.
An: Sure!
Mizuki: More importantly, the pies! They're gonna get cold after we waited so long for them!
Mizuki: Here, An, eat up!
An: Oh, you're right! Here I go!
An: Mmm! What the heck, this is so good!
Mizuki: Nothing beats sugar for a tired brain!
An: You got that right! Thanks for buying these, Mizuki!
Mizuki: You're welcome!
Mizuki: That reminds me! They had a whole bunch of other flavors, like maple syrup and cinnamon!
Mizuki: We should totally go back sometime and try them!
An: Yeah, let's do that! When's good for you?
